<title>Testing API use</title>
<category>testing</category>
<body>

<p>Consider a program to update the labels in a GitHub repo.</p>

<p>Ways to test it:</p>

<ul>
<li>Let the code use GitHub for real, and check the results.</li>
<li>Use a GitHub library, and mock it.</li>
<li>Use requests-mock and mock the GitHub API calls.</li>
<li>Write your own GitHub abstraction, and mock it.</li>
<li>Implement a fake GitHub using requests-mock</li>
    Problems:
        - JQL search can be difficult to mock well.
<li>Implement a fake GitHub as a separate http process.</li>
</ul>

</body>
